<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–2749: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Strong</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-27T12:00:00+07:00">October
                                    27, 1949—noon.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 27—4:46 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Cantel 1231. October 26, Foreign Minister Yeh said that in interview
                            about 10 days ago between Nehru and Chinese Ambassador Koo,<note n="53" xml:id="d169fn53">V. K. Wellington Koo, Chinese Ambassador in the
                                United States.</note> Nehru declared, despite heavy pressure from
                            British, Indian Government would not recognize Chinese Communists for 2
                            or 3 months at which time Nehru opined Chinese Nationalist regime would
                            be finished. Nehru gave as reason for delay in recognition appreciation
                            Chinese help to India in 1942 and past Kuomintang financial and other
                            support to Congress Party.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Strong</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>